[Amit Varma]: But specifically for a moment, let's first talk about the history of Indian sport.

01:48:44.080 --> 01:48:48.800
[Amit Varma]: We've already discussed about how we weren't a sporting nation for a large period of time.

01:48:48.800 --> 01:48:53.360
[Amit Varma]: And there are many reasons one can speculate upon that poverty being one we didn't mention

01:48:53.360 --> 01:48:56.880
[Amit Varma]: because you know, hey, who's got the leisure time to actually play sport.

01:48:56.880 --> 01:49:01.800
[Amit Varma]: But looking back on it, it seems that a lot of the sports that we became good at our essentially

01:49:01.800 --> 01:49:07.200
[Amit Varma]: a colonial bequest, like whether it's cricket or badminton, or we had world champions in

01:49:07.200 --> 01:49:11.760
[Amit Varma]: like billiards and all at one particular point in time, I remember when I was growing up,

01:49:11.760 --> 01:49:16.800
[Amit Varma]: it would seem that these were colonial bequests, which could essentially be played by the anglicized

01:49:16.800 --> 01:49:17.840
[Amit Varma]: elites.

01:49:17.840 --> 01:49:20.360
[Amit Varma]: And then gradually that started changing.

01:49:20.360 --> 01:49:22.840
[Amit Varma]: And now of course, the landscape is very different.

01:49:22.840 --> 01:49:26.160
[Amit Varma]: One narrative, of course, is that liberalization opened it up and there was this burgeoning

01:49:26.160 --> 01:49:27.340
[Amit Varma]: middle class.

01:49:27.340 --> 01:49:32.640
[Amit Varma]: So you had all your cricket stars, you know, coming out of smaller towns, like Dhoni and

01:49:32.640 --> 01:49:37.960
[Amit Varma]: Sehwag and whatever instead of from specific places like I did an episode with the historian

01:49:37.960 --> 01:49:41.720
[Amit Varma]: Ram Goha, where he was speaking about his time in the Hindu college in Delhi in the

01:49:41.720 --> 01:49:43.040
[Amit Varma]: early 70s.

01:49:43.040 --> 01:49:46.800
[Amit Varma]: And it seems the other Indian cricket team was from his college only, you know, so you

01:49:46.800 --> 01:49:52.000
[Amit Varma]: had a very small pool of elite anglicized elite people from whom you are drawing all

01:49:52.000 --> 01:49:54.120
[Amit Varma]: of your talent and that kind of change.

01:49:54.120 --> 01:49:58.800
[Amit Varma]: So take me through a bit of Indian sporting history, did we have a sporting history before

01:49:58.800 --> 01:49:59.800
[Amit Varma]: colonialism?

01:49:59.800 --> 01:50:02.280
[Amit Varma]: Or I mean, do we know anything about that?

01:50:02.280 --> 01:50:07.120
