01:50:07.120 --> 01:50:09.160
[Amit Varma]: And perhaps after liberalization?

01:50:09.160 --> 01:50:11.440
[Amit Varma]: What do you think are the kind of key moments?

01:50:11.440 --> 01:50:14.520
[Amit Varma]: Give me a sense of that direction and that drift.

01:50:14.520 --> 01:50:21.760
[Guest 2]: Okay, I'll just go first, because I used to do this professionally, for I take classes

01:50:21.760 --> 01:50:23.760
[Guest 2]: in IIM Calcutta and MICA.

01:50:23.760 --> 01:50:27.160
[Guest 2]: So this is one of the things that you know, not classes, guest lectures, but this is one

01:50:27.160 --> 01:50:30.800
[Guest 2]: of the things that I always wanted to do, because, see, the one question all of us come

01:50:30.800 --> 01:50:35.880
[Guest 2]: and, you know, all of us have heard this over the last 30 years is that if India has 1 billion

01:50:35.880 --> 01:50:37.960
[Guest 2]: people, why don't we win more medals?

01:50:37.960 --> 01:50:41.600
[Guest 2]: The only way the question hasn't changed is from 1 billion, we've gone to 1.3 billion

01:50:41.600 --> 01:50:43.320
[Guest 2]: and the question has remained the same.

01:50:43.320 --> 01:50:46.400
[Guest 2]: I mean, I hope, you know, in the last five years, the question has changed a little bit

01:50:46.400 --> 01:50:50.280
[Guest 2]: thanks to this kind of stuff that Nandan and his team are doing.

01:50:50.280 --> 01:50:54.680
[Guest 2]: But see, if you look at it, I mean, forget about, you know, Pachisi and, you know, all

01:50:54.680 --> 01:50:58.540
[Guest 2]: the ancient Indian sports, Koko, Pachisi, Koko was apparently played with chariots and

01:50:58.540 --> 01:50:59.540
[Guest 2]: all that.

01:50:59.540 --> 01:51:00.880
[Guest 2]: And there's a lot of history.

01:51:00.880 --> 01:51:06.320
[Guest 2]: But really, Indian sport, as we know, it started with the Brits.

01:51:06.320 --> 01:51:11.600
[Guest 2]: And they just thought that it's a better idea that we sort of throw javelins and, you know,

01:51:11.600 --> 01:51:16.400
[Guest 2]: kick footballs and hockey sticks, use hockey sticks rather than, you know, basically go

01:51:16.400 --> 01:51:17.760
[Guest 2]: to war.

01:51:17.760 --> 01:51:22.600
[Guest 2]: And if you look at it very carefully, you will see that almost every sport, the first

01:51:22.600 --> 01:51:27.120
[Guest 2]: tournament is in the UK, because Brits are very good at, not so good at playing a sport

01:51:27.120 --> 01:51:29.080
[Guest 2]: created in vending sports.

01:51:29.080 --> 01:51:31.180
[Guest 2]: So the first tournament is in the UK.

01:51:31.180 --> 01:51:33.080
[Guest 2]: And the second tournament is in India.

01:51:33.080 --> 01:51:37.200
[Guest 2]: So the first golf course in the world is, of course, the St. Andrews Golf Course in

01:51:37.200 --> 01:51:38.200
[Guest 2]: Scotland.

01:51:38.200 --> 01:51:41.880
[Guest 2]: The next one is the RCJC, which is the Royal Calcutta Golf Club in Calcutta.

01:51:41.880 --> 01:51:46.440
[Guest 2]: The first, you know, major tournament, international football tournament is the FA Cup.

01:51:46.440 --> 01:51:50.640
[Guest 2]: The second is the Durand Cup, which is in India, which is originally played in Shimla.

01:51:50.640 --> 01:51:53.080
[Guest 2]: So for them, the colonial legacy is a great thing.

01:51:53.080 --> 01:51:56.720
[Guest 2]: You keep your, you know, you keep your Brits in India happy.

01:51:56.720 --> 01:51:58.640
[Guest 2]: You keep your soldiers happy.

01:51:58.640 --> 01:52:03.240
[Guest 2]: You keep even the local populace happy, because you know what, I'd rather be beaten in a football

01:52:03.240 --> 01:52:08.400
[Guest 2]: game in 1911 by Mohun Bagan and for people to celebrate, rather than have Bengalis irate

01:52:08.400 --> 01:52:10.320
[Guest 2]: Bengalis throw bombs at me.

01:52:10.320 --> 01:52:11.680
[Guest 2]: And that's the difference.

01:52:11.680 --> 01:52:15.000
[Guest 2]: So the Brits did a very good job of it, which also meant that the sports that they were

01:52:15.000 --> 01:52:20.560
[Guest 2]: interested in were the sports that we really inherited, which is really lots of football,

01:52:20.560 --> 01:52:24.060
[Guest 2]: some amount of cricket, some amount of hockey, that's what we inherited.

01:52:24.060 --> 01:52:25.640
[Guest 2]: And they started putting together tournaments.

01:52:25.640 --> 01:52:30.760
[Guest 2]: So they had this whole tournaments of, you know, the pentangular, where, you know, it's

01:52:30.760 --> 01:52:35.240
[Guest 2]: a costly thought today, but you know, you're playing against religions, you know, Europeans

01:52:35.240 --> 01:52:40.960
[Guest 2]: playing against Parsis, playing against Hindus, playing against Muslims, playing against others,

01:52:40.960 --> 01:52:45.320
[Guest 2]: which is, you know, all other religions which are there and, you know, for example, Vijay

01:52:45.320 --> 01:52:49.500
[Guest 2]: Hazare is an Indian Christian, so he plays for others because he can't play for Europeans.

01:52:49.500 --> 01:52:51.080
[Guest 2]: And all these things happen.

01:52:51.080 --> 01:52:55.720
[Guest 2]: But basically what happens is the British are running sport in India.

01:52:55.720 --> 01:52:58.760
[Guest 2]: Now the big story is what happens in 1947.

01:52:58.760 --> 01:53:01.600
[Guest 2]: So 47 happens, the Brits leave India.

01:53:01.600 --> 01:53:06.520
[Guest 2]: Now you can understand the Brits have, you know, depleted our treasury and all our reserves

01:53:06.520 --> 01:53:07.520
[Guest 2]: over 200 years.

01:53:07.520 --> 01:53:13.480
[Guest 2]: You know, they've had a lot of time, 190 odd years, 1757 to 1947 to do what they do.

01:53:13.480 --> 01:53:18.040
[Guest 2]: Who is left who has the money and time to do anything other than roti kapra makhan,

01:53:18.040 --> 01:53:21.840
[Guest 2]: which is what the country is looking to do because, you know, we are a very poor nation

01:53:21.840 --> 01:53:23.800
[Guest 2]: struggling to, you know, get up.

01:53:23.800 --> 01:53:27.600
[Guest 2]: The only people who had the time were the Maharajas and the Rajas.

01:53:27.600 --> 01:53:31.240
[Guest 2]: So if you look around at that time, you know, half hour trophies, whether it's a Durand,

01:53:31.240 --> 01:53:35.240
[Guest 2]: whether it's, you know, the Patiala, the Ranji trophy, which is presented with the Maharaja

01:53:35.240 --> 01:53:39.880
[Guest 2]: Patiala, all these are dominated by the Maharajas because they are the only people who have

01:53:39.880 --> 01:53:42.040
[Guest 2]: the time and the leisure to do this stuff.

01:53:42.040 --> 01:53:46.260
[Guest 2]: In fact, if you look at it, we shot for a long time, you know, Karni Singh and all these

01:53:46.260 --> 01:53:51.440
[Guest 2]: guys shot for a long time, we did well at Polar because, hell, these are games at Maharajas.

01:53:51.440 --> 01:53:56.280
[Guest 2]: So 1956, we win the World Polar Tournament because, you know, Maharajas do well at that.

01:53:56.280 --> 01:54:00.360
[Guest 2]: We do well at Billiards because, you know, these are the kind of games the Brits play.

01:54:00.360 --> 01:54:05.040
[Guest 2]: So for a long time, this happened and then, you know, 60s, 70s, you're bureaucrats and

01:54:05.040 --> 01:54:07.840
[Guest 2]: everyone's coming in, then what happens?

01:54:07.840 --> 01:54:10.800
[Guest 2]: Then is the next step where Privy Purse happens.

01:54:10.800 --> 01:54:15.760
[Guest 2]: And once the Privy Purse happens, immediately these guys don't no longer have the money.

01:54:15.760 --> 01:54:18.480
[Guest 2]: Look, this is a very, you know, broad stroke narrative.

01:54:18.480 --> 01:54:22.420
[Guest 2]: Secondly, the Indian bureaucracy is also saying that, you know, we want the power.

01:54:22.420 --> 01:54:27.800
[Guest 2]: And remember, in the 70s, possibly the kind of money you would get for, for example, going

01:54:27.800 --> 01:54:32.680
[Guest 2]: abroad is $20, $20 is what you used to get it for an exchange.

01:54:32.680 --> 01:54:36.300
[Guest 2]: So going for a foreign trip abroad was a huge thing.

01:54:36.300 --> 01:54:41.860
[Guest 2]: So the next people who took over this thing were the politicians and the bureaucrats.

01:54:41.860 --> 01:54:45.800
[Guest 2]: Because hey, sport was a way we could send relatives abroad, where you could go abroad,

01:54:45.800 --> 01:54:48.080
[Guest 2]: where you could pet people, and a lot of them.

01:54:48.080 --> 01:54:53.240
[Guest 2]: I'm not saying they were not good people who were there, but a lot of these places, if

01:54:53.240 --> 01:54:58.800
[Guest 2]: you see the Indian sporting establishment, the bureaucracy started dominating it.

01:54:58.800 --> 01:55:03.040
[Guest 2]: And if you see, you know, people like Vijay Kumar Malhotra, you know, Vijay Kumar Malhotra

01:55:03.040 --> 01:55:09.360
[Guest 2]: joined the Indian, you know, Archery Federation in the 70s when Mrs. Gandhi was in power.

01:55:09.360 --> 01:55:14.680
[Guest 2]: And, you know, cut to 2018 and her grandson is, you know, competing for a place and, you

01:55:14.680 --> 01:55:18.760
[Guest 2]: know, trying to, you know, establish his political position.

01:55:18.760 --> 01:55:19.760
[Guest 2]: And he was still in power.

01:55:19.760 --> 01:55:22.560
[Guest 2]: I mean, he just he was there for the next 47, 48 years.

01:55:22.560 --> 01:55:24.880
[Guest 2]: And that's, that's true of so many Indian sports.

01:55:24.880 --> 01:55:29.040
[Guest 2]: I mean, and this is cuts across party lines, you know, whether I want to talk about Jagdish

01:55:29.040 --> 01:55:35.080
[Guest 2]: Title or Sajjan Kumar, all these people, federations were a way of keeping relatives happy of going

01:55:35.080 --> 01:55:37.960
[Guest 2]: for foreign visits and of doing all that.

01:55:37.960 --> 01:55:44.880
[Guest 2]: And I have to say that the really professional Indian managers, sports manager, really is

01:55:44.880 --> 01:55:51.200
[Guest 2]: a product of 2005, 6, 7, 8, you know, up to and including that first IPL.

01:55:51.200 --> 01:55:55.800
[Guest 2]: People like Nandan, people like even a Sundar Raman, you know, entering Indian sport and

01:55:55.800 --> 01:55:58.480
[Guest 2]: saying, OK, we're going to look at it professionally.

01:55:58.480 --> 01:56:05.640
[Guest 2]: So there have been places before, but I think those, those were inflection points, 2008,

01:56:05.640 --> 01:56:10.680
[Guest 2]: the Privy Purse, independence before that, you know, that's, that's basically how I look

01:56:10.680 --> 01:56:11.680
[Guest 2]: at it.

01:56:11.680 --> 01:56:12.680
[Guest 2]: So this is my broad, broad stroke.

01:56:12.680 --> 01:56:15.840
[Guest 2]: I know Nandan will know far more detail and give you a far better idea.

01:56:15.840 --> 01:56:19.400
[Guest 2]: But broadly, these are the ways, you know, you can divide it up.

